Of course, I'm ready for your test interview. Please go ahead with your questions.

Of course, I understand your concern about privacy. I will make sure to keep the microphone off while I read out the questions. Thank you for bringing that up. Now, let's move on to the interview. 

Can you please tell me about your experience with interviews in the past? Have you had any memorable or challenging interview situations?
well I guess I've had some situations where the interviewer refuses to just talk with sentences they just answer yes or no and you have pretty short interview that way

I'm sorry to hear about your experience with those types of interviews. Communication is essential in an interview to truly understand each other. Can you share with me more about how these interviews made you feel or how you handled them?

all right that made me feel good I like talking to new people even if they're challenging most people are are great and you can just ask a simple question and just stop and listen and pull out all the information you need so I do enjoy the interviews
It's great to hear that you enjoy talking to new people and find most of them to be great. What do you find most rewarding about conducting interviews with people?
I like meeting the people the most I think that's fun and just hearing their stories I try to go to their backgrounds and then people are just interesting

That's great to hear that you enjoy meeting new people and learning about their stories. Can you tell me more about why you find people's backgrounds and stories so interesting? What captivates you the most during these interactions?
Thank you for participating in this interview. Is there anything else you would like to add or any final thoughts before we conclude?
